President Obama has declared a major disaster in the U.S. Virgin Islands and authorized federal aid to assist in the recovery efforts after Hurricane Earl struck the area from August 29-31, 2010. The funding will be available for emergency work, as well as the repair or replacement of damaged facilities on the islands of St. Croix, St. John, St. Thomas, and Water Island. Additionally, federal funding will be provided for hazard mitigation measures in these areas. Philip E. Parr has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations. Further designations may be made if requested by the U.S. Virgin Islands and based on damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.